# Pulumi Best Practices for OCR Platform

## Overview

This project uses Pulumi IaC with TypeScript for deploying to Google Cloud Run. Below are best practices for infrastructure management.

## Project Structure

```
infra/
├── Pulumi.yaml              # Pulumi project config
├── Pulumi.dev.yaml          # Stack-specific config (gitignored)
├── Pulumi.prod.yaml         # Production stack config
├── package.json             # Node.js dependencies
├── tsconfig.json           # TypeScript config
├── index.ts               # Main entry point
├── artifact-registry.ts   # Container registry setup
├── cloudrun.ts            # Cloud Run v2 service
├── iam.ts                 # IAM permissions
└── README.md             # Deployment documentation
```

## Commands

### Setup

```bash
cd infra

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Login to Pulumi (local state for simplicity)
pulumi login --local

# Create stack
pulumi stack init dev

# Configure stack
pulumi config set gcp:project YOUR_PROJECT_ID
pulumi config set gcp:region us-central1
pulumi config set ocr-platform:environment dev
```

### Deployment

```bash
# Preview changes
pulumi preview

# Deploy (builds Docker, pushes to Artifact Registry, deploys Cloud Run)
pulumi up

# Destroy all resources
pulumi destroy
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Use Cloud Run v2 API

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use gcp.cloudrunv2.Service
const service = new gcp.cloudrunv2.Service("ocr-service", {
    location: region,
    template: {
        spec: {
            containers: [{ image: imageUri }],
        },
    },
});

// ❌ AVOID - Classic gcp.cloudrun.Service (deprecated features)
const oldService = new gcp.cloudrun.Service("old-service", { ... });
```

### 2. Enable APIs Before Use

```typescript
// Always enable required APIs first
const enableCloudRun = new gcp.projects.Service("enable-cloudrun", {
    service: "run.googleapis.com",
});

const service = new gcp.cloudrunv2.Service("my-service", {
    // ...
}, { dependsOn: [enableCloudRun] });
```

### 3. Separate Project for IaC

For production, use separate GCP projects per environment:

```bash
# Separate projects per environment
gcloud projects create ocr-platform-dev
gcloud projects create ocr-platform-prod
```

### 4. Use Artifact Registry (Not GCR)

GCR was deprecated March 2025. Use Artifact Registry:

```typescript
const registry = new gcp.artifactregistry.Repository("ocr-repo", {
    location: "us-central1",
    repositoryFormat: "docker",
    mode: "STANDARD_REPOSITORY",
});
```

### 5. Build and Push in IaC

Let Pulumi build the Docker image as part of deployment:

```typescript
const image = new docker.Image("ocr-image", {
    imageName: pulumi.interpolate`${region}-docker.pkg.dev/${project}/${registry.name}/ocr:latest`,
    build: {
        context: "..",           // From project root
        dockerfile: "../Dockerfile",
        platform: "linux/amd64", // Required for GCP
    },
});
```

### 6. Scale to Zero for Cost Efficiency

```typescript
scaling: {
    minInstanceCount: 0,  // Scale to zero when idle
    maxInstanceCount: 10,
},
```

### 7. Use Pulumi ESC for Secrets

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Reference secrets from Pulumi ESC
const config = new pulumi.Config();
const apiKey = config.requireSecret("api-key");

// ❌ AVOID - Hardcoded secrets
const apiKey = "super-secret-key"; // Never do this!
```

### 8. Use Config for Environment-Specific Values

```typescript
const config = new pulumi.Config();
const environment = config.get("ocr-platform:environment") || "dev";
const region = config.get("gcp:region") || "us-central1";
```

### 9. Export Important Outputs

```typescript
export const serviceUrl = service.urls;
export const imageUri = image.imageName;
export const artifactRepoUrl = registry.repositoryUrl;
```

### 10. Use Stack Configurations

**Pulumi.dev.yaml:**
```yaml
config:
  ocr-platform:environment: dev
  gcp:region: us-central1
```

**Pulumi.prod.yaml:**
```yaml
config:
  ocr-platform:environment: prod
  gcp:region: us-central1
```

Deploy with:
```bash
pulumi stack select prod
pulumi up
```

## Docker Image Best Practices

### Use Multi-Stage Builds

Your Dockerfile already follows this pattern. Key points:

```dockerfile
# Stage 1: Dependencies
FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm AS backend
RUN uv sync --frozen --no-dev

# Stage 2: Build frontend
FROM node:20-alpine AS frontend
RUN npm ci && npm run build

# Stage 3: Runtime (small)
FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm AS runtime
COPY --from=backend /app ./
COPY --from=frontend /app/frontend/dist ./
```

### Image Size Optimization

- Use `--no-dev` and `--no-install-project` in Docker builds
- Use slim base images (debian-slim, alpine)
- Clean up apt cache (`rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`)

## Cloud Run Configuration

### Recommended Settings

```typescript
{
    ingress: "INGRESS_TRAFFIC_ALL",
    template: {
        scaling: { minInstanceCount: 0, maxInstanceCount: 10 },
        containers: [{
            image: imageUri,
            resources: {
                limits: {
                    cpu: "2",
                    memory: "2Gi",
                },
            },
            ports: { containerPort: 8000 },
        }],
    },
}
```

### Port Mapping

Cloud Run expects port 8080 by default. Your app uses 8000, so specify:

```typescript
ports: { containerPort: 8000 },
env: [{ name: "PORT", value: "8000" }],
```

## IAM Best Practices

### Use Non-Authoritative IAM

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use IamMember for adding permissions
const iam = new gcp.cloudrun.IamMember("public-access", {
    service: service.name,
    role: "roles/run.invoker",
    member: "allUsers",
});

// ❌ AVOID - IamPolicy replaces entire policy
const policy = new gcp.cloudrun.IamPolicy("policy", {
    // ... replaces all existing policies
});
```

### Service Account Least Privilege

```typescript
// Create dedicated service account
const sa = new gcp.serviceaccount.Account("ocr-sa", {
    displayName: "OCR Platform Service Account",
});

// Grant only required roles
new gcp.serviceaccount.IamMember("artifact-reader", {
    serviceAccountId: sa.email,
    role: "roles/artifactregistry.reader",
});
```

## Troubleshooting

### Image Build Fails
```bash
# Test locally first
cd ..
docker build -t test .

# Check Dockerfile path in Pulumi
build: {
    context: "..",
    dockerfile: "../Dockerfile",  // Must be relative to context
}
```

### Pulumi State Issues
```bash
# Refresh state from cloud
pulumi refresh

# Export state
pulumi stack export > state.json

# Import state (if needed)
pulumi stack import < state.json
```

### Permission Errors
```bash
# Ensure gcloud is configured
gcloud auth login
gcloud auth configure-docker us-central1-docker.pkg.dev

# Check IAM permissions
gcloud projects get-iam-policy YOUR_PROJECT
```

